<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd1034409-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e" identifier="/us/usc/t50/s858"><num value="858">§ 858.</num><heading> Applicability to Canal Zone</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This subchapter applies to and within the Canal Zone.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idd103440a-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-01/ch849/s10">Aug. 1, 1956, ch. 849, § 10</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/87/845/s13">Pub. L. 87–845, § 13</ref>, <date date="1962-10-18">Oct. 18, 1962</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/76A/700">76A Stat. 700</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idd103440b-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idd103440c-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="idd103440d-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For definition of Canal Zone, referred to in text, see <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s3602/b">section 3602(b) of Title 22</ref>, Foreign Relations and Intercourse.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idd103440e-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was not enacted as part of the Internal Security Act of 1950 which comprises subchapters I to III of this chapter.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idd103440f-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idd1034410-47c4-11f1-8bcf-c89722bddd2e"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1963-01-02">Jan. 2, 1963</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/87/845/s25">section 25 of Pub. L. 87–845</ref>, set out as an Effective Date of 1962 Amendment note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s414">section 414 of Title 28</ref>, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure.</p>
</note>
</notes>
